<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-594-368  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 594 368.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  June 26 1990 n1454* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services (England) 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New applications for old with Alex language. (System StrategiesLtd. developing Alex language for X Windows)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   System Strategies Ltd. (product development).andO;Product:   ALEX (Program development software) (product development).andO;Topic:     Computer Systems IntegratorsSoftware PublishersProgramming LanguagesX Windows (Standard)Operating EnvironmentsProgram Development ToolsProduct Development.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>NEW APPLICATIONS FOR OLD WITH ALEX LANGUAGEandM;System Strategies Ltd, the Wwest London-based software outfit that struck upa deal with ATandamp;T at the recent Xhibition in San Jose, has been talking aboutits Alex - A Language Extension to X - product, which it says will enablecorporate data processing departments to write graphics front-ends to theirexisting character-based applications, which may be running anywhere on thenetwork.andP;  Although it is a language - looking somewhat like C - in its ownright, Alex avoids the complex task of grappling with the X toolkit itself,by modelling the overall structure and control flow of existing applicationsand matching it to the new graphics version running on an X-terminal orworkstation.andP;  The original program is unchanged, and receives back from Alexcharacters that it can interpret.andP;  The ATandamp;T deal specifies the Open Lookinterface, but System Strategies has an OSF/Motif version waiting in thewings, and claims that a number of further large OEM agreements are to beannounced shortly.andO;</TEXT></DOC>